stigatoractivist and later expelled him for his ideologically uncommitted stance and refusal to subject his observations to censorship. His activities as a fascist were often mundane: leafleting, distributing food parcels to the indigent, and attending public rallies. In Sacrifice, Orsini describes from within the masculine ethos of the militias, the groups' relations with local police and politicians, and the central role of violence and anticommunist actions in building a sense of fascist community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEthnologyxItalyxItaly. 0aEthnologyzItaly. 0aFascismx1945-xItaly. 0aFascismzItalyy1945-. 0aFascistsxSocial conditionsx21st centuryxItaly. 0aFascistszItalyxSocial conditionsy21st century. 0aMilitia movementsxHistoryx21st centuryxItaly. 0aMilitia movementszItalyxHistoryy21st century. 4aEurope. 4aItaly. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh  aneofascist movement, political extremism, Europe's political fringe, fascist community, violence in society, voices of militants.1 aNodes, Sarah J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501709630?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501709630/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles